body:
We Didn’t Realize

[TW: Major Character Deaths]

A quiet raspy breath.

Tony stared at Steve as the other’s blood dripped from his mouth, into a small pool under his cheek and jaw. He wasn’t dead yet, he was still breathing. JARVIS was reading a pulse on Steve, faintly and slowly, from what Tony could hear from the thick pulsing of his own heart in his ears.

The battlefield around them was broken down and dusty, crumbles of rock and asphalt under Tony’s broken down suit. The gold of it was covered in red, stained with blood that was still slowly gushing out of Tony’s deep and wide wound. Tony was still staring at Steve, too tired to move, too scared to say anything, too worn to breathe. He could see how the light in his friend’s eyes was dying out, the cheerful baby blue that once was gathered in those eyes was now cold, reddened from a few tears that accidentally slipped out.

The shield lay broken somewhere aside, dust gathering it and scratched over the star. The red and blue were indistinguishable, all a mix of a dull grey and maroon red. Tony opened his mouth to speak but found himself wheezing for the last of his breath, his fingers crawling gently against the rumble of the road.

Their friends far away, their enemies further, leaving the last of what Captain America and Iron Man was to die slowly. They didn’t blame the other Avengers, they had a fight to finish. One that wasn’t anymore theirs.

Steve tried to move, but any folding of his stomach made the blood leak out again, staining the blue suit with more fresh blood. He coughed, looking at the quiet but sweet and painful eyes opposite of him, relaxed and full with tears. Amber.

Tony could read every emotion in Steve’s face, no more hidden behind a constant frown or a clenched jaw. I’m sorry, I was wrong, forgive me, we weren’t supposed to fight, you were my friend. As consolation, Tony gently nodded as if he was accepting Steve’s apology, and laid there with him with the next few minutes who were passing painfully slow. Too many words unsaid, not enough time to say them. I was in love with you.

Their life was flashing before their eyes. From the first memory to the last, from the first word to the last. Steve remembered the mornings when he’d find Tony in the laboratory, tired and scruffy, scratching at his beard as he tried to think clearly. When Tony laughed so brightly and smiled so much his eyes crinkled at the corners, when his hair looked too fluffy to comprehend, when his hands needily grabbed at every book and tool he could see.

Tony remembered when Steve’s face lit up when he understood film references, remembered his pissed face and half open mouth as he fumed with anger in their little arguments (and the big ones), his bravery, his hiding behind the shield that rightfully belonged to him.

Steve mustered enough strength to pull Tony slightly closer, just enough so he can again feel the fluff of his brown and now graying hair, so he can feel the little broken breaths against his face. Steve whimpered, almost growled as he couldn’t talk, trying to apologize, trying to let out a sound. His panicked eyes were even wider now but Tony looked calm.

“It’s o-okay..” Tony whispered a bit breathlessly, the tears he had been holding back for a while now finally slipping down and rolling from the wrinkles and bags under his eyes, over his button nose and on the cold concrete under them. Steve took in a sharp breath, watching as the suit slowly powered off.

“T..ony..”

“I wanted to go.”

With the last effort and last breath, the few seconds that Steve could hold himself awake, he watched as Tony closed his coffee eyes and smiled just a little, enough for a wrinkle to appear on his face. Steve tightened his hand against Tony’s waist, hissing and letting out little sounds of protest, trying to wake him up. He wasn’t breathing.

Steve, worn and alone, stared at Tony as long as he could. The wounds hurt less than this emptiness in his heart. His shattered breath mingled around them for a few more times untill he finally froze, and the world started turning black. His pulse went low and he couldn’t hear anything else except his own, last thoughts.

For these last moments, when Steve finally let out his last breath and didn’t let himself go before seeing Tony’s peaceful face for the last time, Steve realized that suddenly -

Steve Rogers and Tony Stark were in love, but they didn’t realize. Untill the end.

blog.name: davidmann95
blog.title: Not Even 50% Of My TRUE Power
blog.description: Comics guy, writer guy, Superman guy

summary: I think Aaron's avengers really improved with the latest Issue?
question: I think Aaron's avengers really improved with the latest Issue?
answer: Noticeably! It’s still on the low end of his work, but this really felt like a Jason Aaron Comic for a change rather than a cashed paycheck or a weird retro experiment gone wrong, and I hope it speaks to better things to come. Ed McGuiness is still woefully misapplied for this arc though - Paco Medina’s art in here was tremendously more evocative, and I hope he becomes the regular going forward as someone on a not-dissimilar wavelength to Mcguiness who’s clearly more in tune with what Aaron’s going for.

title: Avengers 4'te Hangi Karakterler Dirilecek? (Ağır Spoiler İçerir)
body:
Avengers 4'te Hangi Karakterler Dirilecek? (Ağır Spoiler İçerir)

Avengers: Infinity War, büyük bir soykırıma sahne olarak sevilen pek çok süper kahramanın kül olup uçmasına neden olmuştu. Fakat biliyoruz ki bazı kahramanlar Avengers 4 ile birlikte Marvel Evreni’ne geri dönecek. Peki hangi karakterler dirilecek ve bu karakterler nasıl hayata geri dönecekler? Bu soruların yanıtları Ant-Man ve Wasp filminde yanıt bulmuş olabilir.

Başta Marvel hayranları olmak…

Thor: My brother will gladly come.

Loki: I will not you dogytdafhcdguk ghu

summary: On my way home from seeing Infinity War, the radio started playing “Another One Bites the Dust”. I still think about that every...
body:
On my way home from seeing Infinity War, the radio started playing “Another One Bites the Dust”.

I still think about that every day. 

Wondering if it was truly “just a coincidence”, or if the djs were conspiring against me, personally targeting me in my most vulnerable moments.
